                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1572">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/42.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Hostetter</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-31T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 31, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Embassy, Mexico City, telegraphs as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>German subjects, according to German Minister, have suffered in Territory
                            of Tepic from depredations by Constitutionalists. German Minister states
                            Constitutionalists have said that they are in connection with Carranza;
                            that he has given orders that property of Americans should be respected
                            because of the nonrecognition by the United States of the Huerta
                            Government, but that the property of other nations is to be treated
                            without respect.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Bring foregoing to attention of proper Constitutionalist authorities with earnest
                    recommendation that they take immediate steps to remedy this situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
